---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Methodology | Rhysora"
  description="How Rhysora ensures every synthetic data value is trustworthy, sourced, and reproducible."
>

  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Methodology</div>
      <h1>How we ensure Rhysora's synthetic data is trustworthy.</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="methodology-body">
    <div class="container prose">
      <p class="lead">
        Synthetic data has a credibility problem. Most tools in this space
        generate values from statistical distributions with no record of where
        those values came from. When a reviewer asks "where did this figure
        come from?", the honest answer is often "the model made it up."
      </p>

      <p class="lead"><strong>Rhysora is built differently.</strong></p>

      <div class="principle">
        <h2>Every value is sourced.</h2>
        <p>
          Clinical thresholds, drug doses, reference ranges, prescribing
          patterns, mortality rates, regional prevalences. All traceable to
          published sources: NICE guidelines, the British National Formulary,
          ONS statistics, NHS published datasets, and the peer-reviewed
          pharmacoepidemiology literature. Values we cannot source are flagged
          as estimates. Nothing is invented.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="principle">
        <h2>Output is reproducible.</h2>
        <p>
          Run Rhysora twice with the same settings, on any computer, and you get
          the exact same dataset. A colleague running it on their machine can
          reproduce your work perfectly from the settings alone. This matters
          because your findings can be independently verified by anyone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="principle">
        <h2>Adversarial review is continuous.</h2>
        <p>
          Rhysora outputs are routinely audited against published standards,
          including pharmacoepidemiology best practice and NICE reference case
          methods. Findings are logged, triaged, and addressed in versioned
          releases.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="caveat">
        <h2>Caveat</h2>
        <p>
          Rhysora is synthetic data. It is not real patient data and is not a
          substitute for studies that require real patient data. It is suitable
          for methodology development, pre-study planning, education, EHR
          testing, and research where synthetic cohorts are explicitly
          acceptable. It is not suitable as a substitute for real-world
          evidence where regulators require real data.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-block">
        <h3>Want to see this in practice?</h3>
        <p>
          Get in touch for a walkthrough of the methodology and a sample extract.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact us →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-12);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    max-width: 780px;
  }

  .methodology-body {
    padding: var(--space-16) 0;
  }

  .prose .lead {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .prose .lead strong {
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .principle {
    padding: var(--space-8) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .principle:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .principle h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .principle p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .caveat {
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
    border-radius: 10px;
  }

  .caveat h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .caveat p {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .cta-block {
    margin-top: var(--space-16);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .cta-block h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .cta-block p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }
</style>
